1 interested parties;
2 (h) One (1) individual who represents the residential long-term care industry,
3 appointed by the Governor from a list of names of qualified persons submitted
4 by any interested parties;
5 (i) One (1) individual who represents providers of adult day care services,
6 appointed by the Governor from a list of names of qualified persons submitted
7 by any interested parties;
8 (j) One (1) individual who represents the home care providers, appointed by the
9 Governor from a list of names of qualified persons submitted by any
10 interested parties;
11 (k) One (1) individual employed by and representing an organization that
12 advocates solely on behalf of physicians, appointed by the Governor from a
13 list of names of qualified persons submitted by any interested parties;
14 (l) One (1) individual employed by and representing an organization that
15 advocates solely on behalf of nurses, appointed by the Governor from a list of
16 names of qualified persons submitted by any interested parties;
17 (m) One (1) individual who conducts research regarding Alzheimer's disease or
18 other dementias, appointed by the Governor from a list of names of qualified
19 persons submitted by any interested parties;
20 (n) One (1) individual who represents an organization that advocates solely on
21 behalf of individuals living with Alzheimer's disease or other dementias,
22 appointed by the Governor from a list of names of qualified persons submitted
23 by any interested parties; and
24 (o) One (1) individual representing a statewide organization that advocates on
25 behalf of Kentuckians aged fifty (50) or older, appointed by the Governor
26 from a list of names of qualified persons submitted by any interested parties.
27 (3) Members who are not state employees shall be reimbursed for necessary and actual
