1 expenses.
2 (4) The council shall meet at least quarterly and at other such times as it determines
3 necessary to perform its duties. A majority of the members shall constitute a
4 quorum for the transaction of the council's business.
5 (5) The council shall:
6 (a) Elect its own chairperson and establish other officers and subcommittees as
7 needed to execute the duties of the council;
8 (b) Adopt bylaws and operate under its bylaws;
9 (c) By December 1, 2029, and by December 1[Starting on July 1, 2021, and
10 repeating] every four (4) years thereafter[after that date], submit an updated
11 Kentucky Alzheimer's and Related Dementias State Plan to the Legislative
12 Research Commission for referral to the Interim Joint Committee on
13 Health Services[Governor for his or her approval and thereafter make it
14 available to the General Assembly]. If the council determines that
15 amendments need to be made to the state plan, an amended Kentucky
16 Alzheimer's and Related Dementia State Plan may be presented to the
17 Legislative Research Commission for referral to the Interim Joint
18 Committee on Health Services[Governor for review and approval];
19 (d) Beginning December 1 of each year, develop and implement a year-long
20 initiative that advances a key area of the Kentucky Alzheimer's and Related
21 Dementias State Plan. The key area to be addressed each year shall be
22 determined by a vote of the council, unless otherwise provided by law.
23 Completed initiatives may be reviewed by the council annually. After review,
24 at the discretion of the council, completed initiatives may be updated as
25 necessary;[Starting on July 1, 2021, and repeating every year after that date,
26 submit an annual report on the implementation progress of the Kentucky
27 Alzheimer's and Related Dementias State Plan to the Governor. This annual
